eadlocks and promote the hell out of yourself.It\'s a great little car that needs a good owner.\nSold.','full_html'),('node','car',0,703,703,'und',0,'This top 10 Bathurst 1000 finisher.Raced as a Group 1 and Gp 2 (C) car.All the top gear used.Race by the great Colin Bond.In good, original order, with a CAMS (FIA) COD.More details coming soon.','full_html'),('node','car',0,704,704,'und',0,'Has the coveted Ferrari Classiche documentation.Looks trick in Fly Yellow.Factory RHD.Trophy winner.Well known car in Ferrari Dino circlesBuilt to drive and show.Chassis #03042.SOLD.','full_html'),('node','car',0,705,705,'und',0,'Very rare opportunity.1991 spec means no exra weight or turbo restrictions.Ultra iconic Nissan works livery.Known history, having raced in 3 different countries and series.Project has been overseen by creators and Nissan maestro\'s, Gibson Motorsport. Needs completion, finish to your standards with GMS keen to help.SOLD.','full_html'),('node','car',0,706,706,'und',0,'1st owner was famous kiwi Ron Butler, of Shelby American fame.Matching numbers.In excellent condition.Housed in one of Australia\'s greatest Porsche collections.Rare oportunity to buy a 356 legend.SOLD.','full_html'),('node','car',0,707,707,'und',0,'Australian delivered 1978 (1979 MY) 911 SC basis.Looks great as small bumper 1971 ST.Factory silver and matching numbers.Goes hard and sounds damn good for a CIS car?Perfect classic daily driver.Chassis #9119300124. ','full_html');
